    "client_msg_id": "692cf6eb-8d8d-439a-9067-5b84db53b818",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "And that's kind of what I meant. Something like making a fast algorithm will always be relegated to the people who study how to make fast algorithms, and as long as we need those, we'll need programmers. But in my experience, the useful apps are just tools to collect and view information, and we shouldn't need millions of programmers making thousands of ad-hoc apps that all do about the same thing and with no interoperability.",
